{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17509139","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17509139"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:13:34+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:13:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11384"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11384","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11384"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.16,0.12,0.09,0.51,0.11]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4029"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78725"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4029","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4029"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11384"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64068"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"13"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"106"},{"type":"tags","id":"1036"},{"type":"tags","id":"1674"},{"type":"tags","id":"2228"},{"type":"tags","id":"2771"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"9627"},{"type":"tags","id":"9735"},{"type":"tags","id":"10964"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"4508"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6718"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7318"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26998"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42584"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44277"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78725","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78725"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 55-year-old is admitted under the general medicine unit for community acquired pneumonia requiring intravenous amoxicillin. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHer medical history is significant for atrial fibrillation and congestive heart failure secondary to chemotherapy (fludarabine, cyclophosphamide, rituximab) for chronic lymphocytic lymphoma diagnosed 2 years previously, and has been in remission for 6 months. She takes amiloride for her congestive heart failure and was recently started on amiodarone for her atrial fibrillation. She states that she was previously taking digoxin however this was stopped by her general practitioner several months ago. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EToday, a \u0027code blue\u0027 is called on the ward for unresponsiveness and hypotension, with her ECG shown below.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following medications is most likely to predispose the patient to this presentation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Digoxin","Cyclophosphamide","Amoxicillin","Amiodarone","Amiloride"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe ECG above exhibits torsades de pointes, a polymorphic ventricular tachycardia predisposed by prolonged QT syndrome (LQTS). Metabolic disturbances that cause a long QT interval are hypokalaemia, hypomagnesaemia, hypocalcaemia. \u003Cstrong\u003EAmiodarone\u003C/strong\u003E causes hypokalaemia and is hence the most likely cause. \u003Cstrong\u003EDigoxin\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Eamiloride \u003C/strong\u003Ecause hyperkalaemia and so are less likely to contribute. \u003Cstrong\u003ECyclophosphamide\u003C/strong\u003E (alkylating agent) is cardiotoxic and can prolong QT intervals. However, the timeline of ceasing it at least 6 months ago does not fit the current presentation. \u003Cstrong\u003EAmoxicillin\u003C/strong\u003E has no effect on QT intervals.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Metabolic disturbances that cause a long QT interval are hypokalaemia, hypomagnesaemia, and hypocalcaemia.","Amiodarone is known to prolong the QT interval, increasing the risk of torsades de pointes."],"references":["\u0022File:12leadTorsade (CardioNetworks ECGpedia).jpg\u0022 by CardioNetworks: [https://www.google.com/search?client=safari\u0026rls=en\u0026q=CardioNetworks+ECGpedia).jpg%22+by+CardioNetworks\u0026ie=UTF-8\u0026oe=UTF-8 ] is licensed under CC BY-SA 3.0.","Cohagan B, Brandis D. Torsade de Pointes. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK459388/","Khan IA. Twelve-lead electrocardiogram of torsades de pointes. Tex Heart Inst J. 2001;28(1):69. PMID: 11330748; PMCID: PMC101137. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC101137/","Johnston J, Pal S, Nagele P. Perioperative torsade de pointes: a systematic review of published case reports. Anesth Analg. 2013 Sep;117(3):559-564. doi: 10.1213/ANE.0b013e318290c380. Epub 2013 Jun 6. PMID: 23744954; PMCID: PMC3750104. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC3750104/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64068"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11384"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20052"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"20052","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20052"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/43836656-9dad-4003-ba06-524e4cad9609.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/43836656-9dad-4003-ba06-524e4cad9609.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":800,"height":384}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64068","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64068"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-12T15:04:43+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-12T15: